AppointmentReminderJob
  #perform
    when appointment is not found
      returns silently without sending any message
    when appointment is cancelled
      skips without sending any message
    when client has no phone
      skips without sending any message
    when client has blank phone
      skips without sending any message
    when all conditions are met for sending
      sends a reminder message via WhatsAppService
      includes the service description
      includes the scheduled time
      includes the address
      includes the provider name
    when appointment has no address
      sends the reminder without an address line
      does not include the address marker
    when appointment has no description
      uses a fallback description
    when client has no name
      sends a generic greeting without the client name
  message tone and format
    uses no more than 2 emojis
    keeps the message within 5-6 lines

FacebookTokenRefreshJob
  #perform
    delegates to FacebookOAuthService.refresh_expiring_tokens
    when there are providers with expiring tokens
      calls refresh_expiring_tokens which processes each provider
    when no providers have expiring tokens
      completes without errors
  job configuration
    uses the default queue

MorningSummaryJob
  #perform
    when an active provider has no WorkDay for today
      sends a morning message via WhatsAppService
      includes a warm greeting with the provider name
      asks about the day in an explicit and instructive way
    when an active provider already has a WorkDay for today (idempotency)
      does not send any message
    when the provider is inactive
      does not send any message
    when the provider has pending tasks from the previous day
      includes the pending tasks in the message
      shows the count of pending tasks
      formats tasks as a bullet list
    when the provider has a single pending task
      uses singular form for one pending task
    when the provider has no pending tasks
      sends a greeting without task list
      does not mention pendientes de ayer
      still asks about new tasks for today
    when multiple active providers need summaries
      sends a message to each provider
  message tone and format
    when there are no pending tasks
      uses no more than 2 emojis
      never scolds the provider
    when there are pending tasks
      uses no more than 2 emojis
      never scolds the provider

PaymentReminderJob
  #perform
    when a provider has outstanding jobs
      sends a payment reminder via WhatsAppService
      includes the total outstanding amount
      includes the client name with their outstanding balance
    when a provider has no outstanding jobs
      does not send any message
    when outstanding amounts are grouped by client
      lists each client with their outstanding balance
      shows the combined total outstanding
    when a provider has multiple outstanding jobs for the same client
      sums the outstanding amounts for the same client
      shows the total outstanding across all jobs
    when a provider has outstanding jobs for different clients
      lists all three clients with their balances
      shows the combined total for all clients
    when no providers have outstanding jobs
      does not send any message
    when a client has no name
      uses a fallback name for the client
  message tone and format
    uses no more than 2 emojis
    keeps the message within 5-6 lines
    includes a warm greeting with the provider name

ReviewRequestJob
  #perform
    when job is not found
      returns silently without sending any message
    when client has no phone on record
      skips without error
    when client has blank phone
      skips without error
    when review already sent
      skips without sending a message
    when max attempts (3) reached
      stops and does not send further messages
    when all conditions are met for sending
      sends review request message via WhatsAppService
      instructs the client to respond with a number
      includes a greeting with the client name
      increments review_attempts and sets review_requested_at
    when rescheduling after a successful attempt
      reschedules for the next 11am CDMX delivery when under max attempts
    when at max attempts after incrementing
      does not reschedule
    when client has no name
      sends a generic greeting without the client name
  .calculate_delivery_time
    always returns a time in the Mexico City timezone
    always returns a time at exactly 11:00:00
    when completed at 10:00 am CDMX
      schedules for 11:00 am CDMX the next day (24h window pushes past same-day 11am)
    when completed at 11:00 am CDMX exactly
      schedules for 11:00 am CDMX two days later (not at exact 24h mark)
    when completed at 11:30 am CDMX
      schedules for 11:00 am CDMX two days later
    when completed at 3:00 pm CDMX
      schedules for 11:00 am CDMX two days later
    when completed at midnight CDMX
      schedules for 11:00 am CDMX the next day
    when completed at 10:59 am CDMX
      schedules for 11:00 am CDMX the next day
    when completed in a different timezone (UTC)
      correctly converts and schedules at 11:00 am CDMX

