JobRegistrationService
  Case 1: Known client, full payment
    looks up the client via ClientLookupService
    creates a Job with status paid
    creates an income Transaction
    enqueues ReviewRequestJob with scheduled delivery time
  Case 2: Unknown client
    delegates client creation to ClientLookupService
  Case 3: Partial payment
    creates a Job with status partial
    creates a Transaction for the paid amount only
    enqueues ReviewRequestJob for partial payment
  Case 4: No payment received
    creates a Job with status pending
    does not create a Transaction when paid_amount is zero
    does not enqueue ReviewRequestJob for pending jobs
  Case 5: Material expense
    when expense is for a specific job
      creates an expense Transaction associated to the job
    when expense is general (no specific job)
      creates an expense Transaction with assigned_to general
  transaction_type safety
    always uses transaction_type: income for job payments
    always uses transaction_type: expense for material expenses

